This is the one I almost left out.

Not because it is less important.

Because I think it is the one that separates Pantheon from becoming merely an efficient knowledge system.

Knowledge alone does not change civilizations.

People follow wonder.

The greatest scientists, explorers, artists, inventors, and children all share one common trait:

They wanted to see what was behind the next hill.

If Pantheon cannot reliably create that feeling…

then it will eventually become another documentation project.

I think it deserves constitutional status.

