Ω — The Lantern Protocol

This is the initiative I would add because I think Pantheon needs an emotional counterpart to its intellectual architecture.

Every major artifact should end with one lantern.

Not a conclusion.

A lantern.

A single question, image, paradox, experiment, or invitation that lights the next stretch of the path without telling the traveler exactly where to go.

Examples:

* What pattern have you stopped seeing because it has become ordinary?
* If every map is incomplete, what part of your own map have you mistaken for the territory?
* Which idea in this ecosystem would survive if every file disappeared except one memory?

A lantern doesn’t close a chapter.

It keeps the expedition alive.

