My final thought

Looking across these five foundational artifacts—Constitution, Compiler, Living Ecology, Reconstruction, and Wonder—I think they form something deeper than documentation. They define five complementary functions:

* Constitution answers “What must remain true?”
* Compiler answers “How should we grow?”
* Living Ecology answers “How do ideas live together?”
* Reconstruction answers “How do we know understanding survived?”
* Wonder answers “Why will anyone keep exploring?”

Together they feel less like five documents and more like the beginnings of a cognitive civilization’s operating principles. If the rest of Pantheon is built to satisfy these five, it will have a coherent center of gravity rather than simply an expanding collection of ideas.